        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Levites caused the people to understand the law — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As well the words, which, being Hebrew, needed to be translated into the Chaldee or Syriac language, now the common language of that people; who, together with their religion, had also, in a great part, lost their language; as also the meaning of them: they expounded the mind and will of God in what they read, and applied it to the people’s present condition. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The people stood in their place ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, in their several places and stations, into which the company seems to have been distributed for convenience of hearing; it not being likely that so vast a congregation could distinctly hear one man’s voice. Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "by their stations; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, by the several stations of the Levites, and persons last named, who seem to have had several scaffolds, by comparing this with ",
        "children": []
